Description: Fragment of handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine pink-buff. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Production date: 199 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 142.)
Curator's comments: Name Pausanias. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria Museum ABC0397.21, which is assigned to Pausanias II; the fragment here seems earlier.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0828)
